Global web inventor plans to launch new internet to take over Google and Facebook
Tim Berners-Lee, inventor of the World Wide Web, is launching a project that could compete with Facebook, Amazon and Google.
Technology legend's latest project, Inrupt, is a company based on the Burners-Lee open-source platform Solid.
Solid allows users to choose where to store their data and which people are allowed access to what information.
In an exclusive interview with the Fast Company, Burners-Lee joked that Inrupt's hidden intent was to "dominate over the world".
