The app uses "Solid" technology so that people can build their own "personal online data storage" or PTD.
It can include contact lists, to-do lists, calendar, music library, and other personal and professional tools.
It’s like if Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify were all available in the same browser at the same time.
Personal online data storage is unique in that only the user determines who and what kind of information can be accessed.
